instruction:
Computer Skills

This section of the test contains multiple-choice questions, which you must answer by using your computer mouse to select the correct response. Upon answering a question, you can go to the next question by clicking the Next button on the Menu bar.

During this section of the test, if you choose you may skip an item and then later return to that item.

When you are finished, select Submit from the Menu bar. Your Test Administrator may have set a time limit for this test section. If there is a time limit, you will be told how much time you have. If a time limit has been set for this section of the test, you will notice a countdown timer on the Header of the screen, showing the amount of time remaining to complete this section of the test.

questions.questionText: What is a flash drive typically used as?

options.text: An extension of the computer's source of portable storage.
A supplement to the processor's power and speed.
An extra security feature to prevent unauthorized users from logging in.
A means of buffering the computer's CD-ROM drive.

What is the difference between shutting the computer down by unplugging it versus using the shutdown feature from within the operating system?

options.text: Turning off your computer with the shutdown feature increases risk for power surges.
Turning off your computer by unplugging will prevent power surges from occurring.
Turning off your computer with the shutdown feature reduces the chances of damaging operating system files.
Turning off your computer by unplugging reduces the chances of damaging operating system files.

questions.questionText: What is the primary difference between the way information is stored on a CD versus the way information stored on a computer's hard drive?

options.text: Computer hard drives are a more secure storage media than CDs.
CDs store information in analog format while computer hard drives store information in binary.
CDs store information using optical technology, while computer hard drives used magnetism to store information.
Computer hard drives cannot ever truly erase information.

questions.questionText: In general, what will occur to files when the recycle bin has been "emptied"?

options.text: The files will be restored to their original location.
The files will be permanently removed from the computer.

options.text: A copy of the selected file is made on the desktop.

questions.questionText: Why should you avoid using the same password for multiple accounts?

options.text: One security breach could compromise many of your accounts.

questions.questionText: An email was sent to you and multiple other recipients. What is the most efficient method to respond to everyone that was included in the email?
You have received an email attachment of a file that is on the network. What will happen to the file on the network if you edit the attached file and save it locally?

options.text: The file is over-written on the network.
The file remains unchanged on the network.
The file is copied and renamed on the network.
The file is removed from the network.

questions.questionText: If a file is stored on a local hard drive rather than stored it on a network drive, which of the following is true?

options.text: You can access the file when you are not connected to the network.
Anyone can access the file when they are connected to the network.
Anyone can access the file when you are connected to the network.
You can only access the file when you are connected to the network.

questions.questionText: In most e-mail applications, what is a "signature?"

options.text: A legally binding indication of acknowledgement or assent.
A way of notifying senders that you received their e-mail.
A method of approving digital documents for publishing.
A block of text containing information about the sender (e.g., name, title, phone number).

questions.questionText: An email was just received from a client. What is the most efficient way to share this e-mail with others in the department?
A report file was completed and needs to be shared with a colleague through e-mail. What action must be taken to send the report file within an email?

options.text: Add the report file to the subject line of the email.
CC the report file in the email.
Copy the file path to the body of the email.
Attach the report file to the email.

questions.questionText: Which of the following outcomes has occurred when a file from a local computer is uploaded to a FTP server?

options.text: A copy of the file from the FTP is placed on the local computer.
A copy of the file from the local computer is placed on the FTP.
The file is deleted from the local computer and placed on the FTP.
The file is deleted from the FTP and placed on the local computer.

questions.questionText: Which of the following outcomes has occurred when a file from a local computer is downloaded from a FTP server?

options.text: A copy of the file from the FTP is placed on the local computer.
A copy of the file from the local computer is placed on the FTP.
The file is deleted from the local computer and placed on the FTP.
The file is deleted from the FTP and placed on the local computer.
